uses broadcast media
to publicize itself

01:25:00.680 --> 01:25:02.210
is something that's
getting closer

01:25:02.210 --> 01:25:04.290
to the intrinsic
subjectivity of social media

01:25:04.290 --> 01:25:06.530
than we might like to think.

01:25:06.530 --> 01:25:07.480
-Thanks.

01:25:07.480 --> 01:25:09.950
Do you want to
tackle end of theory?

01:25:09.950 --> 01:25:12.890
-Well, the limitation
of big data

01:25:12.890 --> 01:25:14.900
is commercial people
to actually go and do

01:25:14.900 --> 01:25:17.620
something interesting and
meaningful and useful with it.

01:25:17.620 --> 01:25:20.690
I think that's the choke point.

01:25:20.690 --> 01:25:23.890
-In speaking from the
standpoint of psychology,

01:25:23.890 --> 01:25:26.950
it has for the last
50 years been largely

01:25:26.950 --> 01:25:30.220
a theory-driven field, but
I see in the last few years

01:25:30.220 --> 01:25:33.370
these big data are
pushing to be still mostly

01:25:33.370 --> 01:25:36.160
theory, but increasingly
hypothesis-driven.

01:25:36.160 --> 01:25:38.440
So the one thing that one
can do from these focus

01:25:38.440 --> 01:25:41.920
groups of 10 million people
is go not with a theory,

01:25:41.920 --> 01:25:43.660
but to say, hey, I
want to know what

01:25:43.660 --> 01:25:46.520
people are saying about
transpeople or about cell

01:25:46.520 --> 01:25:47.370
phones.

01:25:47.370 --> 01:25:49.140
Let me not come
in with a theory.

01:25:49.140 --> 01:25:52.890
Let me first observe empirically
what's being talked about,

01:25:52.890 --> 01:25:55.290
and then tie that
back to underlying

01:25:55.290 --> 01:25:58.700
theory of personality, or
whichever theory structure you

01:25:58.700 --> 01:25:59.440
want.

01:25:59.440 --> 01:26:02.110
So I think the ability
to generate hypotheses

01:26:02.110 --> 01:26:03.510
is unbelievably powerful.

01:26:03.510 --> 01:26:07.380
It's not just asking a
question to confirm or falsify

01:26:07.380 --> 01:26:08.244
a hypothesis.

01:26:08.244 --> 01:26:09.660
That's a very
different style, one

01:26:09.660 --> 01:26:11.690
that's taken over
in medicine but is

01:26:11.690 --> 01:26:14.980
fairly new to large parts
of the social sciences.

01:26:14.980 --> 01:26:16.020
-Great.

01:26:16.020 --> 01:26:19.580
So that's a good note to end
on, that data cannot speak

01:26:19.580 --> 01:26:20.180
for itself.

01:26:20.180 --> 01:26:21.920
And I want to thank
all these panelists

01:26:21.920 --> 01:26:24.970
for presenting their research.

